<span id="freeTextContainer16109062826033404039">Aaaand after almost a year, I’m finally done with this book! This book has a slow slow pace and follows Kassandra from childhood through to what happens to her after the fall of Troy (spoilers, Troy falls!!). A very fascinating (and fictional) take on the world and characters, with different systems of worship, different Gods and Goddesses, different styles of rule with patriarchies and matriarchies. <br/><br/>Overall, an interesting (and slowww) read, but not a particularly thrilling one.<br/><br/><a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[<br/>O</span></span>
