        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer49414667" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3603573878007894789">I love this book and i hate this book.<br/>I love it because it was haunting, in that even when I wasn&apos;t reading it for a day or a few days, I couldn&apos;t get it out of my head. I was interested in the characters and events.<br/>I love that it showed Kassandra and Penthiselia (spelling?) as strong, independent women who were also very interesting characters that had strong and complex development throughout the story.<br/>I hate this book because, in my opinion, it was hyper-feminist. It went beyond creating stro</span>
  <span id="freeText3603573878007894789" style="display:none">I love this book and i hate this book.<br />I love it because it was haunting, in that even when I wasn't reading it for a day or a few days, I couldn't get it out of my head. I was interested in the characters and events.<br />I love that it showed Kassandra and Penthiselia (spelling?) as strong, independent women who were also very interesting characters that had strong and complex development throughout the story.<br />I hate this book because, in my opinion, it was hyper-feminist. It went beyond creating strong female roles to the point at taking cheap shots and "sterotypical male" themes throughout. <br />I also wonder if the author secretly wishes to be raped, as that was a major theme throughout, having had happend or attempted to happen to Kassandra no less than 3 times, and to Penthiselia as she died. <br /><br />Overall, it was a very interesting take on the Illiads' fall of Troy and the many mythical figures such as the Kentaurs and the Amazons. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3603573878007894789" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


