<span id="freeTextContainer1415644010123465458">This book was pretty abysmal, but I kept reading it anyways bc TROJAN WAR, y&apos;all. Bradley spends ages talking about the minutia of Kassandra&apos;s daily life, and about 1 paragraph each on the important events of Achilles&apos; death, the Trojan Horse, etc. There&apos;s also a ridiculous epilogue where she gets a happy ending (as happy as possible after your ENTIRE family is killed or enslaved, on top of the destruction of your home and everything you hold dear). She&apos;s held up as a strong woman with Amazonian</span>
  <span id="freeText1415644010123465458" style="display:none">This book was pretty abysmal, but I kept reading it anyways bc TROJAN WAR, y'all. Bradley spends ages talking about the minutia of Kassandra's daily life, and about 1 paragraph each on the important events of Achilles' death, the Trojan Horse, etc. There's also a ridiculous epilogue where she gets a happy ending (as happy as possible after your ENTIRE family is killed or enslaved, on top of the destruction of your home and everything you hold dear). She's held up as a strong woman with Amazonian values and I guess she's supposed to be a feminist role model but wow. Bless her heart, but no. What a hot mess.</span>
