        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789022539576" href="/book/show/7495554-dochter-van-troje">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17578780-carmen-thereadingtrashqueen?shelf=problematic-asshole-authors">problematic-asshole-authors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2752105459" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer545631113789607492">I read this years and years ago and absolutely loved it. I&apos;ve been wanting to reread it for ages, as it&apos;s stayed with me always, but turns out I had the title wrong all this time! I thought it was called &apos;Cassandra&apos;, but after a thorough search today I finally found it. Such a shame that I recently also found out about the author&apos;s past. It doesn&apos;t make me love the book any less, but it does give it a bit of a sour taste, and I wonder how I&apos;ll fare on my unavoidable reread.</span>
  <span id="freeText545631113789607492" style="display:none">I read this years and years ago and absolutely loved it. I've been wanting to reread it for ages, as it's stayed with me always, but turns out I had the title wrong all this time! I thought it was called 'Cassandra', but after a thorough search today I finally found it. Such a shame that I recently also found out about the author's past. It doesn't make me love the book any less, but it does give it a bit of a sour taste, and I wonder how I'll fare on my unavoidable reread.</span>
